Scouts
from the Uroku Kingdom
mapping our land.

14
00:03:44,349 --> 00:03:47,227
And their preparation
has begun.

15
00:03:49,312 --> 00:03:51,773
Gather all the clans.

16
00:03:53,859 --> 00:03:55,736
It's time.

17
00:05:16,983 --> 00:05:19,569
<i>(Fumitaka)
Cage of the Lost Clan,</i>

18
00:05:19,653 --> 00:05:22,197
<i>the Ninja Council
requests your presence</i>

19
00:05:22,280 --> 00:05:24,825
<i>for a peace summit
at the Warlord's Temple</i>

20
00:05:24,866 --> 00:05:27,118
<i>in the Great
Eastern Mountains.</i>

21
00:05:52,519 --> 00:05:55,605
<i>Choose four
of your finest
to accompany you.</i>

22
00:05:55,689 --> 00:05:59,442
<i>They should have honor
and live by the Code.</i>

23
00:05:59,526 --> 00:06:05,115
<i>For it will be they who
help usher in a new era
of peace among our kind.</i>

24
00:06:19,129 --> 00:06:24,009
<i>A new age
that will provide safety
and security for our families.</i>

25
00:06:37,731 --> 00:06:39,649
<i>So, bring your strongest,</i>

26
00:06:42,485 --> 00:06:44,237
<i>your smartest,</i>

27
00:06:50,076 --> 00:06:51,828
<i>your fiercest,</i>

28
00:06:54,831 --> 00:06:57,417
<i>and your most talented.</i>

29
00:07:34,287 --> 00:07:36,289
<i>May your journey
be swift.</i>

30
00:07:36,373 --> 00:07:38,124
<i>[engine stalls]</i>

31
00:07:47,175 --> 00:07:49,219
<i>[engine starts]</i>

32
00:07:49,302 --> 00:07:51,179
There we go.

33
00:07:54,057 --> 00:07:56,935
<i>And may wisdom
be your guide.</i>

34
00:08:57,370 --> 00:08:58,955
Remember, this
is a peace summit.

35
00:08:59,039 --> 00:09:01,166
Leave your
weapons behind.

36
00:09:31,029 --> 00:09:33,656
<i>The education system
of our ancestors</i>

37
00:09:33,740 --> 00:09:36,910
was they actually
had to go into a room
and read stuff.

38
00:09:36,993 --> 00:09:39,496
Yeah, nothing
was downloadable
back then.

39
00:09:39,579 --> 00:09:42,582
They had to go
and memorize things.

40
00:10:03,269 --> 00:10:04,854
Is that Becker?

41
00:10:06,064 --> 00:10:07,565
This doesn't look good.

42
00:10:09,692 --> 00:10:11,945
Keep them close,

43
00:10:11,986 --> 00:10:14,197
and stay by me.

44
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:16,199
What about our weapons?

45
00:10:26,793 --> 00:10:29,212
It's a peace
summit, guys.

46
00:10:35,385 --> 00:10:38,555
Fumitaka must be hard up
if he's invited

47
00:10:38,638 --> 00:10:42,350
the...Lost Clan.

48
00:10:43,726 --> 00:10:45,228
Tell me,

49
00:10:45,311 --> 00:10:48,398
is it that
you've lost your way

50
00:10:50,733 --> 00:10:52,986
or lost your honor?

51
00:10:53,069 --> 00:10:56,072
This is a peace summit.

52
00:10:56,156 --> 00:11:00,660
The Lost Honor Clan
makes much more sense
to me now.

53
00:11:04,414 --> 00:11:07,208
Hey.

54
00:11:07,292 --> 00:11:11,171
It's the big deaf
and dumb guy.

55
00:11:11,212 --> 00:11:12,589
<i>[laughter]</i>

56
00:11:15,133 --> 00:11:17,010
How is life

57
00:11:18,845 --> 00:11:20,680
with the honorless?

58
00:11:24,517 --> 00:11:27,103
Feel more
at home there?

59
00:11:29,522 --> 00:11:31,691
Answer me,
you big freak.

60
00:11:39,908 --> 00:11:42,118
Honor the Code.
Your code.

61
00:11:43,536 --> 00:11:45,205
<i>[laughter]</i>

62
00:11:50,043 --> 00:11:52,545
What they say about you
is only partly right.

63
00:11:52,629 --> 00:11:54,047
I know the truth.

64
00:11:56,382 --> 00:11:59,886
You are a liar

65
00:12:01,346 --> 00:12:03,389
and a coward.

66
00:12:14,442 --> 00:12:17,904
No fighting.
We're here for
a peace summit.

67
00:12:17,987 --> 00:12:20,823
You must put your
petty differences aside.

68
00:12:20,907 --> 00:12:23,993
Master Fumitaka
has ordered it.

69
00:12:24,077 --> 00:12:25,245
Now.

70
00:12:30,208 --> 00:12:32,418
Cage

71
00:12:32,502 --> 00:12:35,046
of the Lost Clan.

72
00:12:39,133 --> 00:12:40,677
How have you been?

73
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:42,929
Surviving.

74
00:12:44,305 --> 00:12:47,100
Surviving?
Come on.

75
00:12:47,183 --> 00:12:49,269
It's time to flourish.

76
00:12:49,310 --> 00:12:53,439
Master Fumitaka will be
very pleased to see you.

77
00:12:53,523 --> 00:12:56,359
It's been way
too long, brother.

78
00:12:58,111 --> 00:13:00,280
No weapons
in the bunker.

79
00:13:01,531 --> 00:13:03,866
Relinquish them.
Now.

80
00:13:09,372 --> 00:13:12,709
Who's Captain Uptight
over there?
Hiroshi.

81
00:13:12,792 --> 00:13:15,670
We trained together
under Master Fumitaka.

82
00:13:15,753 --> 00:13:18,798
He was chosen
as a Master's second.

83
00:13:18,881 --> 00:13:22,010
Over you?

84
00:13:22,093 --> 00:13:25,013
I guess
you can't be given everything,
can you, little brother?

85
00:14:31,788 --> 00:14:35,458
[beep]

86
00:14:40,129 --> 00:14:42,548
How far down
does this thing go?

87
00:14:42,590 --> 00:14:45,551
These old bunkers
sometimes went
100 floors down.

88
00:14:45,635 --> 00:14:49,055
Thousands of feet
into the earth.

89
00:14:49,138 --> 00:14:52,225
People lived down here
after the Great War.

90
00:14:52,266 --> 00:14:54,936
Protected them
from the fallout.

91
00:14:57,814 --> 00:14:59,857
[clanking]

92
00:15:01,109 --> 00:15:04,737
Only the 20th floor?

93
00:15:04,779 --> 00:15:08,408
I usually like
my peace summits
at least 50 floors down.

94
00:15:08,449 --> 00:15:11,411
No one has ever come back
from the lower floors alive.

95
00:15:13,913 --> 00:15:15,665
Ooh.

96
00:15:16,749 --> 00:15:18,751
Follow me.

97
00:16:04,589 --> 00:16:06,382
Clan leaders,

98
00:16:06,466 --> 00:16:09,051
I am honored
to present to you

99
00:16:09,135 --> 00:16:12,889
our revered master,
Fumitaka.

100
00:16:12,972 --> 00:16:15,057
[cheering]

101
00:16:28,237 --> 00:16:29,906
Brothers.

102
00:16:29,989 --> 00:16:31,824
Sisters.

103
00:16:31,908 --> 00:16:34,827
Fellow ninja warriors.

104
00:16:34,869 --> 00:16:38,039
<i>Look at </i>

105
00:16:39,874 --> 00:16:43,085
Leaders of the great clans
standing side by side.

106
00:16:45,338 --> 00:16:48,674
Each powerful
in his own right.

107
00:16:48,716 --> 00:16:52,178
<i>Each unique
with his own gift'-</i>

108
00:16:52,261 --> 00:16:56,682
The Southern Clan
with their fire-throwers.

109
00:16:56,724 --> 00:17:01,854
The haunting Specters
of the Eastern Sea.

110
00:17:01,938 --> 00:17:06,526
Mighty Desert Dragons
with an even mightier bite.

111
00:17:06,609 --> 00:17:08,528
[hissing]

112
00:17:08,569 --> 00:17:14,784
The Sirens
with their deadly yet
irresistible allure.

113
00:17:14,867 --> 00:17:19,080
Even the mysterious
Lost Clan

114
00:17:19,163 --> 00:17:21,374
has come from afar.

115
00:17:29,173 --> 00:17:31,717
Brothers and sisters,

116
00:17:33,094 --> 00:17:35,888
I come to you
with grave news

117
00:17:35,930 --> 00:17:38,057
that threatens
our very way of life.

118
00:17:38,099 --> 00:17:42,061
We must come together
as one clan today.

119
00:17:42,144 --> 00:17:45,231
[crowd booing
and complaining]

120
00:17:48,568 --> 00:17:50,736
SHence.

121
00:17:52,071 --> 00:17:56,117
I declare
a year of truce.

122
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:58,828
No clan may harm
another clan.

123
00:17:58,911 --> 00:18:01,163
No ninja may harm
another ninja.

124
00:18:02,540 --> 00:18:04,834
Violation of this truce

125
00:18:04,917 --> 00:18:07,712
will be punishable
by death.

126
00:18:15,261 --> 00:18:18,764
He was caught
scouting our woods.

127
00:18:18,806 --> 00:18:21,142
The Uroku Kingdom
is building an army.

128
00:18:21,225 --> 00:18:24,020
They will attack soon.

129
00:18:24,103 --> 00:18:28,024
One by one
we would have fallen.

130
00:18:28,107 --> 00:18:31,110
But, my brothers
and sisters,

131
00:18:31,152 --> 00:18:33,195
together as one clan,

132
00:18:33,279 --> 00:18:36,949
we are unbeatable.

133
00:18:40,369 --> 00:18:43,164
We are bound
by the Code.

134
00:18:43,247 --> 00:18:46,167
Code of the Clan.

135
00:18:46,250 --> 00:18:48,961
Who will stand
with me?

136
00:18:49,003 --> 00:18:51,464
[cheering]

137
00:18:53,049 --> 00:18:55,885
[crowd chanting]
Fumitaka.
Fumitaka.

138
00:18:57,970 --> 00:19:00,806
Fumitaka.
Fumitaka.

139
00:19:02,224 --> 00:19:04,977
Fumitaka.
Fumitaka.

140
00:19:05,019 --> 00:19:08,981
Fumitaka.
Fumitaka.
Fumitaka.

141
00:19:09,023 --> 00:19:11,651
On this day,

142
00:19:11,734 --> 00:19:16,405
let the peace
begin now.

143
00:19:21,494 --> 00:19:26,165
Fumitaka.
Fumitaka.
Fumitaka.

144
00:19:29,543 --> 00:19:31,337
Master?

145
00:19:35,424 --> 00:19:36,842
Master.

146
00:19:43,391 --> 00:19:44,767
It was that one.

147
00:19:46,602 --> 00:19:48,187
<i>From the Lost Clan.</i>

148
00:19:48,270 --> 00:19:51,065
It was him.
lsaw him
throw it.

149
00:19:51,148 --> 00:19:53,025
<i>I saw it
with my own eyes.</i>

150
00:19:53,109 --> 00:19:56,195
The one called Cage.

151
00:19:56,278 --> 00:19:57,613
Get us the hell
out of here.

152
00:19:59,448 --> 00:20:01,367
Grab them.
Take them down.

153
00:20:24,765 --> 00:20:26,517
<i>[electrical burst]</i>

154
00:20:30,187 --> 00:20:32,148
<i>(Cage)
Get out of here.</i>

155
00:21:21,781 --> 00:21:23,699
<i>[soft click]</i>

156
00:21:23,783 --> 00:21:25,284
Let's go.

157
00:21:39,715 --> 00:21:41,801
Looks like we're a few
weapons short.

158
00:21:44,720 --> 00:21:45,721
<i>[rumbling]</i>

159
00:21:48,849 --> 00:21:49,975
Cage.

160
00:22:21,465 --> 00:22:23,175
Grab their weapons.

161
00:22:23,217 --> 00:22:24,677
Let's keep moving.

162
00:22:24,718 --> 00:22:26,846
<i>My kind
of peace summit.</i>

163
00:22:30,099 --> 00:22:34,019
Master Hiroshi,
you cannot ignore
three witnesses.

164
00:22:34,061 --> 00:22:35,896
Cage must pay
for this.

165
00:22:39,900 --> 00:22:43,571
Bring me Cage...alive.

166
00:22:43,654 --> 00:22:47,783
The clan
that captures him,
will be rewarded.

167
00:22:47,867 --> 00:22:49,910
Bring these men
their weapons.

168
00:23:58,062 --> 00:23:59,605
<i>[screeching]</i>

169
00:23:59,647 --> 00:24:01,148
<i>What was that?
I don't know.</i>

170
00:24:01,231 --> 00:24:02,942
I didn't see it.

171
00:24:05,110 --> 00:24:07,071
<i>[soft hissing]</i>

172
00:24:10,407 --> 00:24:12,701
<i>There's something
out there.</i>

173
00:24:15,663 --> 00:24:16,997
Get in the light.

174
00:25:09,883 --> 00:25:12,011
[hissing]

175
00:25:27,651 --> 00:25:29,278
I'm going
to learn that
from you one day.

176
00:25:30,612 --> 00:25:32,072
<i>[door opens]</i>

177
00:25:37,369 --> 00:25:40,164
Surge, Surge,
Surge, Surge.
Surge.

178
00:25:43,584 --> 00:25:46,211
It's an illusion.
[gasps]

179
00:25:46,295 --> 00:25:50,132
<i>(Cage)
Surge, we're still
200 feel' underground.</i>

180
00:26:21,455 --> 00:26:23,624
Any bright ideas now,
little brother?

181
00:26:26,376 --> 00:26:28,170
Power count.

182
00:26:28,253 --> 00:26:31,757
I spent all mine
getting us off
the summit floor.

183
00:26:31,840 --> 00:26:34,426
Mar?
Full.

184
00:26:34,468 --> 00:26:36,095
Surge?
Thirsty.

185
00:26:36,178 --> 00:26:38,013
Surge.
Full.

186
00:26:40,265 --> 00:26:42,601
<i>Barely time
to make a blue spark.</i>

187
00:26:45,145 --> 00:26:48,774
Did anyone get a look
at the assassin?

188
00:26:48,816 --> 00:26:52,194
No. It all happened
so fast.

189
00:26:53,654 --> 00:26:55,030
It's got to be Becker.

190
00:26:56,281 --> 00:26:57,950
Becker?

191
00:26:58,033 --> 00:27:00,119
How could it be Becker?
You look nothing alike.

192
00:27:00,160 --> 00:27:02,621
The look
on Becker's face
right after.

193
00:27:02,704 --> 00:27:04,957
Like he knew
it was going
to happen.

194
00:27:04,998 --> 00:27:07,292
<i>Well, who would want
Fumitaka dead anyways?</i>

195
00:27:07,376 --> 00:27:09,128
It's Becker.

196
00:27:09,211 --> 00:27:11,380
He doesn't want peace.

197
00:27:11,463 --> 00:27:14,133
He wants us gone.

198
00:27:14,174 --> 00:27:16,802
He kills Fumitaka
and then blames me.

199
00:27:16,885 --> 00:27:19,888
<i>Gives him the excuse
to finally take our
entire village out</i>

200
00:27:19,972 --> 00:27:21,890
<i>while putting him in tight
with the new regime.</i>

201
00:27:21,974 --> 00:27:23,892
Two birds, one stone.

202
00:27:41,827 --> 00:27:44,371
If you turn yourself in,
they'll let the rest
of us go.

203
00:27:44,454 --> 00:27:46,874
I doubt <i>that.
It's worth a shot,
isn't i2'?</i>

204
00:27:46,957 --> 00:27:49,418
We're just waiting
to die down here.

205
00:27:49,501 --> 00:27:51,545
Your loyalty
is appreciated.

206
00:27:51,628 --> 00:27:54,673
You got us
into this mess coming
to this ridiculous summit.

207
00:27:54,756 --> 00:27:56,341
Surge, you're acting
like an idiot.

208
00:27:56,425 --> 00:27:58,177
Oh, I'm an idiot, huh?
I'm an idiot?

209
00:27:58,218 --> 00:28:00,596
Look where it's
gotten us to, huh?
Surge.

210
00:28:04,933 --> 00:28:08,520
How is he going
to hold this clan
together?

211
00:28:10,981 --> 00:28:14,693
Well, at least
I'll be drunk
when we die.

212
00:28:19,740 --> 00:28:22,951
We'll stay alive
by the Code.
Your Code is dead
and so are we.

213
00:28:23,035 --> 00:28:24,620
Our Code
is a commitment.

214
00:28:24,703 --> 00:28:27,456
To the clan.
The village.
Each other.

215
00:28:27,539 --> 00:28:31,710
This isn't about us.
About whether we live.

216
00:28:31,793 --> 00:28:33,545
It's about whether
our wives live,

217
00:28:33,587 --> 00:28:37,382
our children live,
our clan lives.

218
00:28:37,466 --> 00:28:39,468
The Code
is bigger than me.

219
00:28:39,551 --> 00:28:41,345
Bigger than us.

220
00:28:43,597 --> 00:28:45,557
Brother,

221
00:28:45,641 --> 00:28:49,728
we...must be
bigger than us.

222
00:29:45,784 --> 00:29:48,453
Come on.

223
00:29:48,495 --> 00:29:50,247
Let's get out of here.

224
00:30:21,528 --> 00:30:23,238
Let's split up.

225
00:30:23,322 --> 00:30:25,324
I don't think
that's a good idea.

226
00:30:25,407 --> 00:30:27,034
We'll never find
each other.

227
00:30:27,117 --> 00:30:29,369
We've got to cover
more ground.

228
00:30:32,164 --> 00:30:34,041
All right,
let's split up.

229
00:30:34,124 --> 00:30:36,335
But remember this spot.

230
00:30:36,418 --> 00:30:38,337
Get back here in 15.

231
00:31:17,751 --> 00:31:19,544
<i>[lockers crash]</i>

232
00:32:44,004 --> 00:32:45,005
[gasps]

233
00:34:15,387 --> 00:34:16,429
Ahh.

234
00:34:49,462 --> 00:34:52,257
Two on one?
I guess the odds
are even.

235
00:37:02,429 --> 00:37:04,889
[breathing heavily]

236
00:37:21,948 --> 00:37:23,950
Find anything?

237
00:37:24,033 --> 00:37:25,744
Six guarding
a staircase.

238
00:37:25,785 --> 00:37:28,079
Must lead somewhere
they don't want us to go.

239
00:37:28,121 --> 00:37:30,957
Picked up some
presents for you.
Where's Mar?

240
00:37:37,338 --> 00:37:39,424
[panting]

241
00:37:52,270 --> 00:37:53,855
<i>[sword clanks]</i>

242
00:37:57,442 --> 00:37:59,235
<i>[loud clank]</i>

243
00:38:08,036 --> 00:38:09,412
<i>[Clank]</i>

244
00:38:17,295 --> 00:38:18,963
<i>[Mar screaming]</i>

245
00:38:22,133 --> 00:38:23,384
(Cage)
Mar.

246
00:38:23,468 --> 00:38:25,595
Nofirge)

247
00:38:42,320 --> 00:38:44,030
[whimpers]

248
00:38:47,075 --> 00:38:50,745
Mar, guardian
of clan and family.

249
00:38:52,831 --> 00:38:55,583
Your heart

250
00:38:55,667 --> 00:38:58,086
beat with bravery.

251
00:38:58,169 --> 00:39:00,588
Your blood

252
00:39:00,672 --> 00:39:03,341
flowed with sacrifice.

253
00:39:03,383 --> 00:39:06,678
Your death
defined honor.

254
00:39:12,350 --> 00:39:14,143
Peace, my friend.

